<subSubSection id="80F86505FFDCE871F273FACA3314D2D4" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="20" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C85D368EFFDCE871F273FACA3314D2D4" blockId="17.[816,1475,1388,2052]" lastBlockId="19.[113,772,235,739]" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="20" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<bibRefCitation id="AC734B7FFFDCE873F273FACA35CFD5B3" author="PRENDINI L. &amp; S. LORIA" box="[816,1194,1388,1412]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 482" part="442" refId="ref6606" refString="PRENDINI L. &amp; S. LORIA. 2020. Systematic revision of the Asian forest scorpions (Heterometrinae Simon, 1879), revised suprageneric classification of Scorpionidae Latreille, 1802 and revalidation of Rugodentidae Bastawade et al., 2005. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 442: 1 - 482." title="Systematic revision of the Asian forest scorpions (Heterometrinae Simon, 1879), revised suprageneric classification of Scorpionidae Latreille, 1802 and revalidation of Rugodentidae Bastawade et al" type="journal article" year="2020">Prendini &amp; Loria (2020: 442)</bibRefCitation>
formally synonymized 
<taxonomicName id="0FE24D0DFFDCE873F273FA2A35FDD593" authority="KovarIk, 2012" authorityName="KovarIk" authorityYear="2012" box="[816,1176,1420,1446]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lowei">
<emphasis id="FA96EA9CFFDCE873F273FA2A3284D593" box="[816,993,1420,1444]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Pandinus lowei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="AC734B7FFFDCE873F2B0FA2A35FDD593" author="KOVARIK, F." box="[1011,1176,1420,1446]" journalOrPublisher="Euscorpius" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 22" part="141" refId="ref6107" refString="KOVARIK, F. 2012. Review of the subgenus Pandinurus Fet, 1997 with descriptions of three new species (Scorpiones, Scorpionidae, Pandinus). Euscorpius, 141: 1 - 22." title="Review of the subgenus Pandinurus Fet, 1997 with descriptions of three new species (Scorpiones, Scorpionidae, Pandinus)" type="journal article" year="2012">KovařÍk, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
under 
<taxonomicName id="0FE24D0DFFDCE873F5B9FA2A32A3D5F3" authority="Pocock, 1890" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1890" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viatoris">
<emphasis id="FA96EA9CFFDCE873F5B9FA2A34A7D594" box="[1274,1474,1420,1444]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Pandinus viatoris</emphasis>
Pocock, 1890
</taxonomicName>
(both now in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="0FE24D0DFFDCE873F5A7FA0A340ED5F3" authorityName="Rossi" authorityYear="2015" box="[1252,1387,1452,1476]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandipalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FA96EA9CFFDCE873F5A7FA0A340ED5F3" box="[1252,1387,1452,1476]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Pandipalpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), citing only “ 
<emphasis id="FA96EA9CFFDCE873F234FA6A3551D5D3" box="[887,1076,1484,1508]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">unpublished data</emphasis>
” and not providing specific details or analyses to support their taxonomic act. They wrote: “ 
<emphasis id="FA96EA9CFFDCE873F4F1FA4A34A7D653" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
It is also evident, based firstly on the absence of consistent morphological differences, and secondly on low genetic divergence between samples collected at the 
<typeStatus id="1759882CFFDCE873F45DF9EA342FD654" box="[1310,1354,1612,1635]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">type</typeStatus>
locality of
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="0FE24D0DFFDCE873F273F9CA351CD6B3" authority="Kovarik, 2012" authorityName="KovarIk" authorityYear="2012" box="[816,1145,1644,1668]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lowei">
Pandinus lowei 
<emphasis id="FA96EA9CFFDCE873F29EF9CA34A7D6B3" box="[989,1474,1644,1668]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<bibRefCitation id="AC734B7FFFDCE873F29EF9CA351CD6B3" author="KOVARIK, F." box="[989,1145,1644,1668]" journalOrPublisher="Euscorpius" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 22" part="141" refId="ref6107" refString="KOVARIK, F. 2012. Review of the subgenus Pandinurus Fet, 1997 with descriptions of three new species (Scorpiones, Scorpionidae, Pandinus). Euscorpius, 141: 1 - 22." title="Review of the subgenus Pandinurus Fet, 1997 with descriptions of three new species (Scorpiones, Scorpionidae, Pandinus)" type="journal article" year="2012">Kovařík, 2012</bibRefCitation>
, and across the distribution of
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="0FE24D0DFFDCE873F273F92A32FFD693" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1890" box="[816,922,1676,1700]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viatoris">P. viatoris</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="FA96EA9CFFDCE873F2E2F92A35C3D6F4" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">(unpublished data), that these taxa are conspecific, justifying the following synonymy</emphasis>
”. However, the claim of “ 
<emphasis id="FA96EA9CFFDCE873F27FF96A34F1D6D3" box="[828,1428,1740,1764]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">the absence of consistent morphological differences</emphasis>
” is inconsistent with our data. For example, as illustrated in 
<figureCitation id="50D92A0BFFDCE873F4CEF94A3213D713" captionStart="Figures 77–81" captionStartId="17.[115,192,970,992]" captionTargetBox="[113,1468,225,955]" captionTargetId="figure-563@17.[113,1474,222,955]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figures 77–81: Pedipalp chela dorsal views. Figures 77–78. Pandipalpus lowei, male (77) and female (78) paratypes from type locality. Figures 79–81. Pandipalpus viatoris, male (79) and female (80) from Democratic Republic of Congo, Kamonga (FKCP), and male (81) from Tanzania, Iringa Province (FKCP)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4243933" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4243933/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs. 77–81</figureCitation>
, there are pronounced differences in the morphometrics and granulation of the pedipalp chelae of these two species. The 
<taxonomicName id="0FE24D0DFFDCE873F227F8EA32B9D754" box="[868,988,1868,1891]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viatorus">
<emphasis id="FA96EA9CFFDCE873F227F8EA3211D754" box="[868,884,1868,1891]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="FA96EA9CFFDCE873F2C6F8EA32B9D754" box="[901,988,1868,1891]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">viatorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
male from Kamonga, 
<collectingCountry id="B0F5761EFFDCE873F598F8EA32F0D7B3" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Democratic Republic of Congo</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="50D92A0BFFDCE873F2E7F8CA3291D7B3" box="[932,1012,1900,1924]" captionStart="Figures 77–81" captionStartId="17.[115,192,970,992]" captionTargetBox="[113,1468,225,955]" captionTargetId="figure-563@17.[113,1474,222,955]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figures 77–81: Pedipalp chela dorsal views. Figures 77–78. Pandipalpus lowei, male (77) and female (78) paratypes from type locality. Figures 79–81. Pandipalpus viatoris, male (79) and female (80) from Democratic Republic of Congo, Kamonga (FKCP), and male (81) from Tanzania, Iringa Province (FKCP)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4243933" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4243933/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 79</figureCitation>
), a locality relatively close (
<quantity id="0F1A9B6BFFDCE873F460F8CD3412D7B3" box="[1315,1399,1899,1924]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="km" value="250.0">250 km</quantity>
) to the 
<typeStatus id="1759882CFFDCE873F273F82A323BD793" box="[816,862,1932,1956]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName id="0FE24D0DFFDCE873F299F82A3556D793" authorityName="KovarIk" authorityYear="2012" box="[986,1075,1932,1956]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lowei">
<emphasis id="FA96EA9CFFDCE873F299F82A328FD794" box="[986,1002,1932,1955]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="FA96EA9CFFDCE873F2BAF82A3556D793" box="[1017,1075,1932,1956]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">lowei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Lusinga, Parc National de Upemba, 
<collectingCountry id="B0F5761EFFDCE873F273F80A35E1D7F3" box="[816,1156,1964,1988]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Democratic Republic of Congo</collectingCountry>
) has distinctly more elongate pedipalp fingers and weaker manus granulation vs. the 
<taxonomicName id="0FE24D0DFFDCE873F4E8F86A320FD833" authorityName="KovarIk" authorityYear="2012" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lowei">
<emphasis id="FA96EA9CFFDCE873F4E8F86A34DED7D4" box="[1451,1467,1996,2019]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="FA96EA9CFFDCE873F273F84A320FD833" box="[816,874,2028,2052]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">lowei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
male (
<figureCitation id="50D92A0BFFDCE873F2FAF84A356ED833" box="[953,1035,2028,2052]" captionStart="Figures 77–81" captionStartId="17.[115,192,970,992]" captionTargetBox="[113,1468,225,955]" captionTargetId="figure-563@17.[113,1474,222,955]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figures 77–81: Pedipalp chela dorsal views. Figures 77–78. Pandipalpus lowei, male (77) and female (78) paratypes from type locality. Figures 79–81. Pandipalpus viatoris, male (79) and female (80) from Democratic Republic of Congo, Kamonga (FKCP), and male (81) from Tanzania, Iringa Province (FKCP)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4243933" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4243933/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 77</figureCitation>
). The chela of another 
<taxonomicName id="0FE24D0DFFDCE873F44EF84A34E1D834" box="[1293,1412,2028,2051]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viatorus">
<emphasis id="FA96EA9CFFDCE873F44EF84A3478D834" box="[1293,1309,2028,2051]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="FA96EA9CFFDCE873F46EF84A34E1D834" box="[1325,1412,2028,2051]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">viatorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
male (
<figureCitation id="50D92A0BFFDEE871F13AFF4D31AFD134" box="[121,202,235,259]" captionStart="Figures 77–81" captionStartId="17.[115,192,970,992]" captionTargetBox="[113,1468,225,955]" captionTargetId="figure-563@17.[113,1474,222,955]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figures 77–81: Pedipalp chela dorsal views. Figures 77–78. Pandipalpus lowei, male (77) and female (78) paratypes from type locality. Figures 79–81. Pandipalpus viatoris, male (79) and female (80) from Democratic Republic of Congo, Kamonga (FKCP), and male (81) from Tanzania, Iringa Province (FKCP)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4243933" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4243933/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 81</figureCitation>
) is very similar, although it originates from 
<collectingRegion id="0A26F86CFFDEE871F3FEFF4D339AD134" box="[701,767,235,259]" country="Tanzania" name="Iringa" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Iringa</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="B0F5761EFFDEE871F132FEAD31B1D114" box="[113,212,267,291]" name="Tanzania" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
, a locality separated from Kamonga by 
<quantity id="0F1A9B6BFFDEE871F3D7FEAD339AD114" box="[660,767,267,291]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="km" value="1.1">1,100 km</quantity>
. Also very similar is the chela of another male from 
<quantity id="0F1A9B6BFFDEE871F3FFFE8D3266D174" box="[700,771,299,323]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.2" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="km" value="92.0">92 km</quantity>
NW of Mpika, 
<collectingCountry id="B0F5761EFFDEE871F05BFEED300CD154" box="[280,361,331,355]" name="Zambia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Zambia</collectingCountry>
(
<quantity id="0F1A9B6BFFDEE871F03AFEED30A8D154" box="[377,461,331,355]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="km" value="460.0">460 km</quantity>
from Kamonga) (see fig. 
<quantity id="0F1A9B6BFFDEE871F3ABFEED31E3D1B4" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.652" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="in" value="38.0">38 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="AC734B7FFFDEE871F1CCFECD303CD1B4" author="KOVARIK, F." box="[143,345,363,389]" journalOrPublisher="Euscorpius" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 22" part="141" refId="ref6107" refString="KOVARIK, F. 2012. Review of the subgenus Pandinurus Fet, 1997 with descriptions of three new species (Scorpiones, Scorpionidae, Pandinus). Euscorpius, 141: 1 - 22." title="Review of the subgenus Pandinurus Fet, 1997 with descriptions of three new species (Scorpiones, Scorpionidae, Pandinus)" type="journal article" year="2012">KovařÍk, 2012: 12</bibRefCitation>
). This indicates that the morphology is stable over the wide geographic range of 
<taxonomicName id="0FE24D0DFFDEE871F364FE2D33F0D195" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1890" box="[551,661,395,418]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viatoris">
<emphasis id="FA96EA9CFFDEE871F364FE2D3352D195" box="[551,567,395,418]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="FA96EA9CFFDEE871F307FE2D33F0D195" box="[580,661,395,418]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">viatoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="AC734B7FFFDEE871F3E0FE2D31B6D1F4" author="KOVARIK, F." journalOrPublisher="Euscorpius" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 22" part="141" refId="ref6107" refString="KOVARIK, F. 2012. Review of the subgenus Pandinurus Fet, 1997 with descriptions of three new species (Scorpiones, Scorpionidae, Pandinus). Euscorpius, 141: 1 - 22." title="Review of the subgenus Pandinurus Fet, 1997 with descriptions of three new species (Scorpiones, Scorpionidae, Pandinus)" type="journal article" year="2012">KovařÍk, 2012: 19</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 64), and there is no obvious character gradient that links or overlaps with 
<taxonomicName id="0FE24D0DFFDEE871F0C0FE6D30BCD1D4" authorityName="KovarIk" authorityYear="2012" box="[387,473,459,483]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lowei">
<emphasis id="FA96EA9CFFDEE871F0C0FE6D30F6D1D5" box="[387,403,459,482]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="FA96EA9CFFDEE871F0DCFE6D30BCD1D4" box="[415,473,459,483]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">lowei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Other diagnostic characters separating the two species were cited in 
<bibRefCitation id="AC734B7FFFDEE871F365FE4D33AAD234" author="KOVARIK, F." box="[550,719,491,517]" journalOrPublisher="Euscorpius" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 22" part="141" refId="ref6107" refString="KOVARIK, F. 2012. Review of the subgenus Pandinurus Fet, 1997 with descriptions of three new species (Scorpiones, Scorpionidae, Pandinus). Euscorpius, 141: 1 - 22." title="Review of the subgenus Pandinurus Fet, 1997 with descriptions of three new species (Scorpiones, Scorpionidae, Pandinus)" type="journal article" year="2012">KovařÍk (2012)</bibRefCitation>
. The second justification of synonymy by “ 
<emphasis id="FA96EA9CFFDEE871F347FDAD3392D214" box="[516,759,523,547]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">low genetic divergence</emphasis>
“ was not demonstrated in 
<bibRefCitation id="AC734B7FFFDEE871F0C6FD8D33F7D274" author="PRENDINI L. &amp; S. LORIA" box="[389,658,555,579]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 482" part="442" refId="ref6606" refString="PRENDINI L. &amp; S. LORIA. 2020. Systematic revision of the Asian forest scorpions (Heterometrinae Simon, 1879), revised suprageneric classification of Scorpionidae Latreille, 1802 and revalidation of Rugodentidae Bastawade et al., 2005. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 442: 1 - 482." title="Systematic revision of the Asian forest scorpions (Heterometrinae Simon, 1879), revised suprageneric classification of Scorpionidae Latreille, 1802 and revalidation of Rugodentidae Bastawade et al" type="journal article" year="2020">Prendini &amp; Loria (2020)</bibRefCitation>
, and there was no indication that the authors analyzed the 
<typeStatus id="1759882CFFDEE871F32CFDED33C2D254" box="[623,679,587,611]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">types</typeStatus>
of these species. Considering the absence of convincing evidence for synonymy, and the documented morphological differences, we reinstate 
<taxonomicName id="0FE24D0DFFDEE871F041FD0D33ECD2F4" authority="(KovarIk, 2012)" baseAuthorityName="KovarIk" baseAuthorityYear="2012" box="[258,649,683,709]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandipalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lowei">
<emphasis id="FA96EA9CFFDEE871F041FD0D30ABD2F4" box="[258,462,683,707]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Pandipalpus lowei</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="AC734B7FFFDEE871F0A3FD0D33E7D2F4" author="KOVARIK, F." box="[480,642,683,709]" journalOrPublisher="Euscorpius" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 22" part="141" refId="ref6107" refString="KOVARIK, F. 2012. Review of the subgenus Pandinurus Fet, 1997 with descriptions of three new species (Scorpiones, Scorpionidae, Pandinus). Euscorpius, 141: 1 - 22." title="Review of the subgenus Pandinurus Fet, 1997 with descriptions of three new species (Scorpiones, Scorpionidae, Pandinus)" type="journal article" year="2012">KovařÍk, 2012</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
as a valid species distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="0FE24D0DFFDEE871F016FD6D3308D2D4" authority="(Pocock, 1890)" baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[341,621,715,739]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viatoris">
<emphasis id="FA96EA9CFFDEE871F016FD6D30A5D2D5" box="[341,448,715,738]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. viatoris</emphasis>
(Pocock, 1890)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
